the%20Canadian%20Government%20takes%20strict%20and%20verifiable%20action%20against%20those%20who%20actively%20pursue%20anti-India%20activities%20and%20have%20conspired%20to%20promote%20hate%2C%20disinformation%2C%20communal%20disharmony%20and%20violence%20in%20India%20as%20well%20as%20Canada.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETies%20between%20India%20and%20Canada%20are%20at%20an%20all-time%20low%20after%20Justin%20Trudeau's%20allegations%20in%20September%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Bpotential%20involvement%26quot%3B%20of%20Indian%20agents%20in%20Khalistani%20terrorist%20Hardeep%20Singh%20Nijjar's%20killing%20outside%20a%20gurdwara%20in%20Surrey%20city%20on%20June%2018%2C%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20had%20designated%20Hardeep%20Singh%20Nijjar%20as%20a%20terrorist%20in%202020%20and%20has%20strongly%20rejected%20Justin%20Trudeau's%20allegations%20as%20%26quot%3Babsurd%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bmotivated.%26quot%3B%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1728655260000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-10%2Foftq3iv_pm-modi-justin-trudeau-modi-trudeau-ani_625x300_11_October_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fties-cant-be-repaired-unless-india-rejects-justin-trudeaus-claim-as-pms-meet-6768280%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India%20today%20strongly%20rejected%20claims%20made%20by%20Canadian%20PM%20Justin%20Trudeau%20that%20%26quot%3Bsafety%20of%20Canadians%26quot%3B%20was%20discussed%20when%20he%20met%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20in%20Laos%2C%20on%20the%20sidelines%20of%20the%20ASEAN%20Summit.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%2240%20elite%20colleges%20are%20being%20sued%20over%20accusations%20they%20colluded%20to%20increase%20tuition%20by%20%246%2C200%20%26amp%3Bmdash%3B%20primarily%20by%20overcharging%20divorced%20parents%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Cornell%20University%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67082311a70318649280fcb1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222001%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECornell%20University%20is%20among%20the%20schools%20accused%20of%20colluding%20to%20raise%20tuition.%20%3Cp%3EMatt%20Burkhartt%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EForty%20elite%20colleges%20are%20targeted%20in%20a%20new%20lawsuit%20accusing%20them%20of%20colluding%20to%20increase%20tuition.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20lawsuit%20claims%20the%20schools%20are%20factoring%20in%20the%20incomes%20of%20divorced%20parents%2C%20even%20if%20one%20of%20the%20parents%20cannot%20contribute.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThis%20has%20led%20to%20students%20paying%20about%20%246%2C200%20more%20than%20necessary%2C%20the%20lawsuit%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EForty%20elite%20colleges%20are%20facing%20legal%20action%20over%20accusations%20they%20conspired%20to%20raise%20tuition%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0primarily%20by%20targeting%20students%20with%20divorced%20parents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELaw%20firm%20Hagens%20Berman%20filed%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hbsslaw.com%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fcase-downloads%2Fcollege-board-price-fixing-antitrust%2F2024-10-07-complaint.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eclass-action%20lawsuit%3C%2Fa%3E%20earlier%20this%20week%20on%20behalf%20of%20plaintiffs%20Maxwell%20Hansen%20and%20Eileen%20Chang%2C%20former%20students%20of%20Boston%20University%20and%20Cornell%20University%2C%20respectively.%20The%20lawsuit%20targets%20a%20form%20known%20as%20the%20CSS%20profile%20%E2%80%94%20administered%20by%20the%20College%20Board%20%E2%80%94%20that%20some%20schools%20use%20to%20determine%20how%20much%20financial%20aid%20a%20student%20will%20get.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawsuit%20accused%20the%20College%20Board%20of%20an%20%26quot%3Bintentional%20push%26quot%3B%20that%20began%20in%202006%20to%20require%20the%2040%20schools%20named%20in%20the%20case%20to%20consider%20the%20incomes%20of%20divorced%20or%20separated%20parents%20when%20making%20financial%20aid%20decisions.%20This%20enabled%20schools%20to%20produce%20higher%20estimates%20of%20what%20a%20family%20can%20afford%20to%20pay%20for%20tuition%20than%20what%20might%20actually%20be%20feasible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20lawsuit%2C%20considering%20income%20of%20divorced%20parents%20raised%20the%20average%20tuition%20price%20for%20students%20by%20about%20%246%2C200.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BStudents%20were%20told%20there%20were%20no%20exceptions%20to%20the%20requirement%20%E2%80%93%20even%20if%20a%20divorce%20court%20order%20was%20issued%20concerning%20college%20expenses%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20lawsuit%20said.%20%26quot%3BFormulas%20are%20then%20used%20to%20generate%20a%20financial%20aid%20offer.%20The%20student%20then%20ultimately%20receives%20an%20estimate%20for%20the%20family%20contribution%20based%20on%20what%20the%20two%20parents%20can%20contribute%2C%20regardless%20of%20whether%20both%20parents%20do%20actually%20contribute.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20College%20Board%20told%20Business%20Insider%20in%20a%20statement%20that%20it%20%26quot%3Bhas%20just%20received%20this%20legal%20action%20and%20are%20reviewing%20it%2C%20but%20we%20are%20confident%20that%20we%20will%20prevail%20in%20this%20action.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECornell%20University%20and%20Columbia%20University%20declined%20to%20comment%20on%20pending%20litigation.%20Boston%20University%20and%20the%20other%20Ivy%20League%20schools%20named%20in%20the%20case%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20BI%20on%20the%20lawsuit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChang%2C%20one%20of%20the%20plaintiffs%2C%20attended%20Cornell%20from%202017%20to%202021%2C%20and%20she%20submitted%20the%20CSS%20profile%20as%20part%20of%20her%20financial%20aid%20application.%20While%20Chang's%20noncustodial%20parent%20%E2%80%94%20the%20parent%20Chang%20did%20not%20live%20with%20%E2%80%94%20was%20on%20disability%20and%20unable%20to%20contribute%20to%20her%20tuition%2C%20the%20lawsuit%20said%20the%20CSS%20profile%20still%20evaluated%20Chang's%20financial%20aid%20based%20on%20both%20of%20her%20parent's%20incomes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20Chang's%20custodial%20parent%20had%20to%20take%20out%20a%20parent%20PLUS%20student%20loan%20%E2%80%94%20the%20most%20expensive%20type%20of%20federal%20student%20loan%20with%20the%20highest%20interest%20rate%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0to%20pay%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20her%20tuition%2C%20and%20Chang%20faced%20%26quot%3Bartificially%20high%20prices%26quot%3B%20to%20attend%20Cornell%20because%20she%20did%20not%20receive%20the%20right%20amount%20of%20financial%20aid%2C%20the%20lawsuit%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawsuit%20accused%20the%20participating%20schools%20of%20anti-competitive%20behavior%2C%20saying%20that%20they%20%26quot%3Bhave%20substantial%20endowments%20and%20the%20proven%20capacity%20to%20meet%20the%20financial%20needs%20of%20their%20students%20without%20reducing%20their%20endowments%20(if%20that%20were%20even%20imperative)%2C%20and%20without%20colluding%20to%20artificially%20reduce%20financial%20aid.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20isn't%20the%20first%20time%20elite%20schools%20have%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolumbia-yale-brown-financial-aid-collusion-settlement-price-fixing-cartel-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccused%20of%20anti-competitive%20behavior%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%202022%2C%20five%20former%20undergraduates%20of%20Duke%2C%20Northwestern%2C%20the%20University%20of%20Chicago%2C%20Yale%2C%20and%20Brown%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdo-i-qualify-for-university-of-chicago-settlement-financial-aid-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esued%2016%20schools%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20engaging%20in%20a%20%26quot%3Bprice-fixing%20cartel%26quot%3B%20to%20keep%20financial%20aid%20packages%20low.%20Some%20of%20those%20schools%20have%20agreed%20to%20settle%2C%20giving%20millions%20of%20dollars%20back%20to%20students.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felite-colleges-colluding-raise-tuition-for-divorced-parents-student-debt-2024-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1728655218000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F670823203f2165d716dffb68%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felite-colleges-colluding-raise-tuition-for-divorced-parents-student-debt-2024-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Two%20former%20students%20filed%20a%20class-action%20case%20against%2040%20top%20colleges%20over%20claims%20the%20schools%20colluded%20to%20increase%20costs%20and%20exacerbate%20student%20debt.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22asheffey%40businessinsider.com%20(Ayelet%20Sheffey)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felite-colleges-colluding-raise-tuition-for-divorced-parents-student-debt-2024-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Teenager%20among%20four%20dead%20in%20latest%20Russian%20attack%20on%20Odesa%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1728655209000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F56f7%2Flive%2F60fb4ad0-87b0-11ef-b0bd-ed1c890dbbf6.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fclyzpnnwr3jo%230%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20two-storey%20building%20was%20hit%20in%20the%20fourth%20such%20attack%20on%20the%20Black%20Sea%20coastal%20region%20in%20five%20days.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fclyzpnnwr3jo%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fclyzpnnwr3jo.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2F