ercome%20the%20challenges%20of%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-f-16-pilots-had-to-dramatically-change-way-fly-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20flying%20a%20fighter%20very%20different%20from%20the%20Soviet-designed%20jets%3C%2Fa%3E%20Ukraine%20knows%20best.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMichael%20Bohnert%2C%20a%20RAND%20Corporation%20analyst%2C%20said%20that%20integrating%20F-16s%2C%20or%20any%20new%20type%20of%20jet%2C%20into%20an%20air%20force%20%26quot%3Btakes%20a%20lot%20of%20effort%2C%20time%2C%20training%2C%20and%20money%20that%20often%20gets%20overlooked.%20A%20lot%20of%20people%20think%3A%20'Oh%2C%20just%20give%20them%20the%20hardware%20and%20everything's%20okay.'%20Well%2C%20no.%26quot%3B%20The%20hardware%20really%20is%20only%20part%20of%20what%20it%20takes%20to%20build%20a%20fighter%20fleet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERetired%20US%20Army%20Maj.%20Gen.%20Gordon%20'Skip'%20Davis%2C%20who%20served%20as%20NATO's%20deputy%20assistant%20secretary-general%20for%20its%20Defense%20Investment%20Division%2C%20said%20that%20for%20Ukraine's%20F-16%20program%2C%20told%20BI%20%26quot%3Bthe%20big%20issue%20is%20really%20the%20number%20of%20trained%20Ukrainian%20pilots.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226dbaee8a-2faf-4465-840f-ec43eb49112c%5C%22%3ETraining%20bottleneck%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EF-16%20training%20for%20Ukraine's%20pilots%20is%20being%20done%20by%20a%20coalition%20of%20countries%2C%20including%20the%20Netherlands%2C%20Canada%2C%20Denmark%2C%20the%20US%2C%20and%20Romania.%20The%20process%2C%20however%2C%20doesn't%20appear%20to%20be%20as%20smooth%20as%20it%20probably%20could%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBohnert%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bthere%20have%20been%20concerns%20around%20all%20of%20the%20different%20bottlenecks%20that%20we're%20seeing%2C%20including%20the%20training%20spaces%20and%20things%20like%20that%2C%20where%20even%20if%20more%20F-16s%20had%20been%20committed%20to%20Ukraine%20at%20this%20point%2C%20that%20doesn't%20necessarily%20mean%20that%20it%20could%20have%20more%20of%20them%20in%20the%20air.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENorway%2C%20Belgium%2C%20and%20the%20Netherlands%2C%20Denmark%20have%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thedefensepost.com%2F2023%2F12%2F22%2Fdutch-delivery-f16-ukraine%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epledged%20more%20than%2085%20F-16%20jets%20to%20Kyiv%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20Ukraine%20can%20only%20field%20as%20many%20jets%20as%20the%20country%20has%20trained%20pilots.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221801%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20F-16%20fighter%20jets%20flying%20side-by-side%20against%20blue%20skies.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66b2c782b4912df3ae197dec%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221201%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUkrainian%20F-16s%20are%20seen%20in%20the%20air%20in%20an%20undisclosed%20location%20of%20Ukraine%20on%20August%204.%3Cp%3EREUTERS%2FValentyn%20Ogirenko%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20total%20number%20of%20trained%20Ukrainian%20pilots%20and%20those%20still%20undergoing%20training%20is%20not%20officially%20known%2C%20but%20there%20are%20indications%20that%20the%20number%20is%20not%20enough%20for%20Ukraine's%20needs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPolitico%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.com%2Fnews%2F2024%2F06%2F05%2Fukraine-f-16-pilot-training-00161742%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20June%20that%20Ukraine's%20Western%20partners%20did%20not%20have%20the%20number%20of%20training%20spaces%20that%20Ukraine%20wanted%20for%20its%20pilots.%20It%20reported%20that%2030%20Ukrainian%20pilots%20were%20ready%20for%20training%2C%20but%20the%20US%20training%20program%20could%20not%20accept%20them%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20said%20that%20a%20total%20of%2020%20Ukrainian%20F-16%20pilots%20were%20expected%20to%20graduate%20by%20the%20end%20of%20this%20year%20%E2%80%94%20half%20of%20what%20a%20former%20US%20defense%20official%20said%20Ukraine%20would%20need%20to%20operate%20a%20full%20squadron%20of%20jets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Ukrainian%20lawmaker%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thetimes.com%2Fworld%2Frussia-ukraine-war%2Farticle%2Ff-16-fighter-jet-pilots-ukraine-spring-offensive-russia-0dx8p26dp%3Fid%3D1756158124%26gad_source%3D1%26gclid%3DCj0KCQjwsJO4BhDoARIsADDv4vAjEFJLt19g8E8Kyqlsh8Jc02bww0QkMloj8bNG1sovpsTURiGRxXwaAjL6EALw_wcB%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccused%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20US%20of%20%26quot%3Bdeliberately%20delaying%26quot%3B%20training%20and%20creating%20a%20situation%20where%20there%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Bfewer%20trained%20pilots%20than%20fighter%20jets.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkrainian%20President%20Volodymyr%20Zelenskyy%20then%20said%20in%20August%2C%20when%20the%20first%20F-16s%20arrived%20in%20his%20country%2C%20that%20Ukraine%20did%20not%20have%20enough%20trained%20pilots%20or%20enough%20of%20the%20jets%20themselves.%20%26quot%3BThe%20number%20of%20F-16s%20we%20have%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20the%20number%20of%20pilots%20who%20have%20already%20been%20trained%2C%20is%20not%20enough%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20partners%20appear%20to%20have%20training%20restrictions%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ukrainian%20President%20Volodymyr%20Zelenskyy%20stands%20outside%20in%20front%20of%20microphones%20and%20wearing%20a%20black%20long-sleeved%20t-shirt%20with%20a%20Ukrainian%20Air%20Force%20F-16%20fighter%20jet%20behind%20him%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67065b7a3f2165d716df7605%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUkrainian%20President%20Volodymyr%20Zelenskyy%20stands%20against%20the%20background%20of%20Ukraine's%20Air%20Force's%20F-16%20fighter%20jets%20in%20an%20undisclosed%20location%20in%20Ukraine%20on%20August%202024.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FEfrem%20Lukatsky%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDanish%20Defense%20Minister%20Troels%20Lund%20Poulsen%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthedefensepost.com%2F2024%2F06%2F27%2Fdenmark-conclude-pilot-training-ukraine%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20June%20that%20his%20country%20would%20stop%20training%20Ukrainian%20pilots%20on%20the%20fourth-generation%20F-16s%20after%20this%20year%20and%20instead%20focus%20on%20building%20its%20fleet%20of%20fifth-generation%20F-35s.%20That%20raises%20questions%20about%20the%20Ukrainian%20pilots%20in%20the%20training%20pipeline%20and%20opportunities%3Cstrong%3E.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGeorge%20Barros%2C%20a%20Russia%20analyst%20at%20the%20Insitute%20for%20the%20Study%20of%20War%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20number%20of%20airframes%20Ukraine%20has%20is%20limited%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20then%20the%20biggest%20limiting%20factor%20are%20the%20trained%20humans%2C%20the%20pilots%20that%20actually%20fly%20the%20planes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20huge%20pilot%20training%20bottleneck%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2255362b12-f87a-4ee2-853c-82d5642acc17%5C%22%3EGetting%20the%20best%20pilots%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBohnert%20said%20the%20way%20to%20ensure%20Ukraine%20has%20the%20best%20pilots%20flying%20its%20new%20jets%20without%20delaying%20getting%20the%20F-16s%20in%20the%20sky%20is%20to%20train%20more%20pilots%20and%20be%20ruthless%20about%20cutting%20the%20ones%20who%20do%20not%20nail%20the%20training.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine's%20F-16s%2C%20jets%20that%20were%20first%20manufactured%20by%20General%20Dynamics%20before%20that%20task%20later%20passed%20to%20Lockheed%20Martin%2C%20represent%20a%20challenge%20for%20Ukraine's%20pilots%2C%20who%20have%20to%20overcome%20old%20habits%20and%20muscle%20memory%20associated%20with%20flying%20the%20kind%20of%20Soviet-designed%20jets%20that%20exclusively%20made%20up%20Ukraine's%20air%20force%20before%20the%20F-16s%20arrived.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkrainian%20pilots%20were%20given%20around%20nine%20months%20of%20training%2C%20but%20most%20Western%20pilots%20are%20given%20three%20years%20to%20learn%20the%20jets%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Frussia-ukraine-war-f16s-what-to-know-224d96ff2ad4f416d3969676a55876e2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20The%20Associated%20Press.%20That's%20not%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20to%20adapt%20to%20a%20completely%20new%20jet%20that%20is%20much%20more%20sensitive%20with%20fly-by-wire%20controls%20instead%20of%20hydraulic%20ones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20undersides%20of%202%20F-16s%20are%20seen%20flying%20against%20a%20grey%20sky%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67065c5c3f2165d716df761e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221291%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Ukrainian%20Air%20Force's%20F-16%20fighter%20jets%20fly%20in%20an%20undisclosed%20location%20in%20Ukraine%20on%20August%204%2C%202024.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FEfrem%20Lukatsky%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ELikely%20not%20every%20pilot%20is%20up%20to%20the%20task%2C%20and%20that's%20a%20problem.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20train%20someone%20who's%20a%20great%20pilot%20in%20one%20plane%20and%20transition%20'em%20to%20a%20new%20plane%2C%20it's%20a%20hard%20change%20for%20a%20lot%20of%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20Bohnert%20said%2C%20explaining%20that%20the%20solution%20is%20to%20%26quot%3Bput%20more%20pilots%20through%20training.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20there's%20a%20need%20to%20%26quot%3Bget%20a%20higher%20number%20and%20be%20pretty%20clear%20that%20it's%20okay%20to%20wash%20half%20the%20out%20and%20say%3A%20'Sorry%2C%20you're%20not%20good%20enough.%20You%20need%20more%20time.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBohnert%20said%20Ukraine's%20partners%20would%20ideally%20have%20three%20pilots%20being%20trained%20for%20every%20aircraft.%20It's%20not%20clear%20how%20many%20pilots%20are%20being%20trained%20for%20each%20of%20the%20F-16s%20promised%20to%20Ukraine%2C%20but%20it%20appears%20short%20of%20that%20expectation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETraining%20to%20that%20level%20of%20excess%2C%20Bohnert%20said%2C%20would%20give%20Ukraine%20options%20and%20lighten%20what%20is%20already%20a%20heavy%20load%20as%20it%20builds%20its%20new%20fighter%20fleet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2268a56aaa-3bf7-4258-81c2-9106e8fa86bc%5C%22%3EF-16s%20comes%20with%20challenges%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAir%20warfare%20experts%20expect%20the%20F-16s%20to%20be%20a%20big%20boost%20for%20Ukraine%2C%20but%20they%20have%20cautioned%20that%20they%20likely%20won't%20be%20game-changers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine%20is%20receiving%20a%20smaller%20number%20than%20what%20its%20leadership%20and%20partners%20say%20it%20needs%20to%20be%20able%20to%20take%20risks%2C%20like%20the%20West%20does%2C%20and%20challenge%20Russia's%20larger%2C%20more%20capable%20air%20force.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20F-16%20fighter%20jets%20fly%20over%20a%20Patriot%20Air%20and%20Missile%20Defense%20System%20aginst%20a%20grey%20sky%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67065c9d198738e3a70f4756%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Ukrainian%20Air%20Force's%20F-16%20fighter%20jets%20fly%20over%20a%20Patriot%20Air%20and%20Missile%20Defense%20System%20in%20an%20undisclosed%20location%20in%20Ukraine%20in%20August%202024.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FEfrem%20Lukatsky%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBohnert%20said%20the%20number%20of%20F-16s%20Ukraine%20is%20getting%20from%20its%20partners%20is%20%26quot%3Bdefinitely%20not%20enough.%26quot%3B%20Zelenskyy%20said%20in%20May%20that%20his%20air%20force%20needed%20about%20120%20to%20130%20advanced%20fighter%20aircraft%20to%20challenge%20Russia%20in%20the%20air.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20challenges%20that%20Ukraine's%20armed%20forces%20face%20have%20been%20exacerbated%20by%20the%20delay%20in%20their%20arrival%2C%20many%20warfare%20experts%20have%20said.%20Ukraine%20asked%20for%20the%20jets%20soon%20after%20Russia%20launched%20its%20full-scale%20invasion%2C%20but%20the%20US%20long%20refused%20to%20budge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20wait%20for%20permission%20to%20come%20gave%20Russia%20time%20to%20prepare%20and%20meant%20programs%20like%20training%20could%20not%20begin%20earlier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20F-16s%20that%20Ukraine%20is%20receiving%20are%20also%20older%20models%20that%20don't%20come%20with%20the%20latest%20upgrades%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-old-f16s-outclassed-russia-best-jets-former-general-nato-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edon't%20quite%20stack%20up%20against%20some%20of%20Russia's%20best%20jets%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine's%20F-16%20fighters%2C%20despite%20being%20capable%20combat-proven%20platforms%2C%20are%20a%20generation%20behind%20the%20newest%20fighters%2C%20like%20the%20F-35s%20the%20US%20and%20its%20allies%20are%20operating%20or%20Russia's%20Su-57s%2C%20and%20they%20would%20likely%20be%20outmatched%20by%20some%20of%20the%20fourth-gens%20like%20Russia's%20Su-35s.%20And%20without%20the%20stealth%20capabilities%20of%20the%20fifth-gen%20jets%2C%20it's%20also%20vulnerable%20to%20modern%20Russian%20surface-to-air%20missile%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBohnert%20said%20Ukraine's%20newly%20acquired%20F-16s%2C%20which%20the%20US%20Air%20Force%20says%20cost%20somewhere%20between%20%2414%20million%20to%20%2418%20million%2C%20are%20%26quot%3Bolder%20airframes%20with%20not%20a%20lot%20of%20life%20left%2C%26quot%3B%20though%20he%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bdoesn't%20mean%20they're%20bad.%26quot%3B%20It%20just%20limits%20what's%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExperts%20say%20that%20the%20jets%2C%20despite%20their%20limits%2C%20will%20help%20Ukraine%2C%20particularly%20against%20incoming%20drone%20and%20missile%20attacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGordon%20said%20that%20ultimate